description: The gang is ready to quit the garden when they find the weed in the garden has failed, but they discover an abundance of "miracle" green tomatoes.
title: Fried Green Tomatoes

description: Our heroes travel through Compton in a food truck, spreading the good word and fish tacos. When Jesus's phone falls into the wrong hands, Trayvon is desperate to get it back.
title: Taco Sundays

description: When Fish seduces a city worker into a no limit EBT card, he learns that free food can come at a high price.
title: Tasty Tudi's

description: When Vic misinterprets the gang's latest hustle as terrorist activity, he gears up to wage a one-man war against them.
title: False Witness

description: As our heroes start bottling and selling their magical green tomato sauce, Ms. Tudi is presented with a unique opportunity to make peace with Vic and the Concerned Citizens of Southwest Central Compton (CCSWC).
title: Love Thy Enemy, Part 1

description: After being extorted by Mexican gangsters, our heroes are left with no money for fertilizer for their garden, so they must execute a manure heist at the Compton Boarding Stables.
title: The S*** Heist

description: The parole officer for Jesus, a friendly white dude that just wants to make the world a better place, witnesses proof of Jesus' divinity, has a spiritual upheaval and decides to stop going to work and follow Jesus.
title: Parole Officer

description: Jesus returns from jail to discover his running buddy Boonie has relocated from their old Compton Gardens apartment complex to the "New" Compton Gardens, where Lloyd is building manager.
title: The Compton Carter

description: After discovering the leaked video of Jesus performing a miracle, the Vatican sends two secret Vatican agents from Italy to Compton USA to kidnap "the Black Jesus" and determine if this oversized black guy is really the son of God.
title: Vatican Guys

description: Ms. Tudi miraculously scores a small business loan, and now she can open "Tudi's Wigs, Weaves and Whatnots."  The Korean Bitch Mafia isn't happy the store is on their turf, and that means war.
title: Hair Tudi

description: Boonie thinks he has been possessed by the soul of a dead gangster and begins acting like a serious badass.  That day, Lloyd serves Jesus papers - he's taking him to "Homey's Court" for making him sober, and to settle up for $600.
title: Boonie Comes Up

description: AmBro, the head of security at The New Compton Gardens, has formed a militia to scare off drug dealers in the hood.  In a show of force, his troops take over the street for a day, which screws up a drug deal the gang planned for that day.
title: Operation Shut'emdown

description: Jesus lets Boonie have the power of Christ so he can see how difficult being the Son of God really is.  While Boonie is trying to figure out how to make his new powers work for him, Jesus takes a skip day for himself.
title: Boonie Christ

description: There's a vigilante in Southwest Compton, and he's taken matters into his own hands.  Jesus has to stop him before he goes too far.
title: The Compton Crusader

description: Jesus suddenly finds himself as the coach for the Compton Devils junior high football.  His agenda to spread love and kindness is at odd with winning at all costs, and we see his struggle play out in the big game.
title: God's Team

description: The gang talks Jesus into starring in a reality show after a sleazy producer promises them fame and fortune.  It's a disaster from start to finish, but Jesus is determined to get Pop's good word out as a result.
title: The Real Jesus of Compton

description: Please, not MySpace.
title: Jesus' Followers

description: Had to argue those curls.
title: Smooth Talk

description: Advantage Jesus.
title: Homey's Court

description: Trayvon's foray into documentary filmmaking reveals greed, chaos, angry farmers, and a saboteur pouring bleach in the garden.
title: The Other Shoe Drops

description: The gang agrees to help Boonie with a yard sale to get more money for child support, even though he swears he paid.  His ex, Shalinka, shows up to wreak havoc on the sale and our guys.
title: I Gave at the Playground

description: Vic has let the complex fall into shambles - with Lloyd acting as manager.
title: Love Thy Enemy, Part 2

description: Fed up with the commercialization of the holiday, Jesus makes a Christmas wish of his own. When it's granted, he's forced to face the unintended consequences of life without divinity.

input: A Very Special Christmas in Compton

title: A Very Special Christmas in Compton

description: Jesus joins Ms. Tudi in her latest money-making scheme, a mobile spa van charging for Holy foot massages. The hustle puts Fish in an awkward position when Tudi soon decides it better to sell Fish's "gift of sexiness" instead.
title: Hands of God

description: Vic vows to remove Jesus from the neighborhood, and hires Lloyd to be his "eyes and ears in the streets" and keep tabs on him.  Meanwhile Jesus and the gang find the perfect lot for the garden, only to face instant extortion from local Mexican gangsters.
title: Fish and the Con Man

description: Jesus and the gang take on the "Church of Jesus Christ in Compton" and plot to teach its corrupt preacher a lesson.
title: Jesus Gonna Get His

description: When Trayvon's dad hooks them up with free cable, Vic will stop at nothing to spoil the gang's enjoyment of fight night.
title: Janky Cable

description: Vic plunges into sin courtesy of Lloyd's estranged wife. Meanwhile, the gang shoots a music video for Boonie's latest track, "Side Bitches".
title: Thy Neighbor's Strife

description: Lloyd's wife resurfaces announcing she wants a divorce. Vic is overjoyed, until things get messy. After a visit to the probation office, Fish faces a test of faith.
title: Good for Nothing

description: Nobody's perfect, not even your Boy.
title: Season 1 Blooper Reel

description: Fresh from the mental hospital, Jesus is back in Compton looking for a place to stay. He grows concerned when it appears Fish has returned to a life of crime.
title: No Room for Jesus

description: While Jesus is on the run, our gang is left to ponder what would Black Jesus do in their shoes.
title: WTFWBJD

description: The gang talks Jesus into coming along on a drug buy financed by Boonie's mom.
title: Smokin', Drinkin', and Chillin'

description: With a little divine influence, Lloyd gets a lucrative job as a liquor spokesman. Success changes Lloyd but not in the ways Jesus had hoped.
title: Never Say When

description: With the garden in danger, our heroes decide to have an online benefit concert with Coolio to raise the money.
title: Gangsta's Paradise
